.TH MIXERCTL 1 "March, 2026"
.SH NAME
\fBmixerctl\fP \- Control knobs on audio devices.
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBmixerctl\fP [\fB\-d\fP \fIdevice_id\fP] \fB\-l\fP
.br
\fBmixerctl\fP [\fB\-d\fP \fIdevice_id\fP] [\fB\-k\fP \fIknob_id\fP] \fB\-r\fP
.br
\fBmixerctl\fP [\fB\-d\fP \fIdevice_id\fP] [\fB\-k\fP \fIknob_id\fP] \fB\-w\fP \fIknob_value\fP
.SH DESCRIPTION
Controls "knobs" on audio devices. These knobs generally specify the volume of different inputs or outputs.
.TP
.B \-d \fIdevice_id\fP
Specify the audio device to control, by numeric ID.
.TP
.B \-k \fIknob_id\fP
Specify the knob to modify, by numeric ID.
.TP
.B \-l
List the available knobs on the device.
.TP
.B \-r
Read the value of a knob.
.TP
.B \-w \fIknob_value\fP
Set the value of a knob.
.SH DEVICE FILES
This utility interfaces with \fB/dev/mixer\fP.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
0
Knobs were successfully list, read, or written.
.TP
1
An error occurred.

.SH AUTHOR
This utility was written by Mike Gerow.
